# SPEC-070-B AC-25(a). This example ships in TWO public places: the npm tarball (governed by the
# package's `files` allowlist) and the force-pushed public git mirror (`git subtree split`, which
# carries the entire committed history regardless of `files`). Nothing secret may ever be committed
# here — inject at build time via launch args / env, exactly as the Flutter example does.

# ── Demo-tenant secrets. NEVER commit. ──────────────────────────────────────
**/GoogleService-Info-AppDNA.plist
**/google-services-appdna.json
**/appdna-config.json
.env
*.env
appdna-demo-key*

# Android signing + machine-local SDK paths.
#
# `android/app/debug.keystore` is EXEMPT and committed on purpose: it is Android's universally-known
# public debug key, byte-identical on every machine, and it cannot sign a Play release. Every RN
# template ships it. Without it `:app:packageDebug` fails. Release keystores stay ignored.
*.keystore
*.jks
!android/app/debug.keystore
**/local.properties
**/key.properties

# ── Build artefacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.log
*.swp

# Metro / Babel
.metro-health-check*
.expo/
dist/

# iOS
ios/Pods/
ios/build/
ios/DerivedData/
ios/.xcode.env.local
*.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/
*.xcodeproj/xcuserdata/
.swiftpm/

# Android
android/build/
android/app/build/
android/.gradle/
android/.idea/
android/app/debug
android/app/release
*.iml
*.hprof

# RN codegen output
android/app/build/generated/
ios/build/generated/
